{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "stone", "icon": "VOP/stone", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Stone"], "extent": [61, 71]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Simulates a rough, non-descript stone material."], "extent": [71, 127]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator simulates a rough, non-descript stone material."], "extent": [127, 190]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The stone displacement consists of noisy bumps and cavities, whose\nrandomness is controlled by Bump Frequency (", {"type": "code", "text": ["bfreq"]}, "), Bump Amplitude\n(", {"type": "code", "text": ["bamp"]}, ") and Bump Roughness (", {"type": "code", "text": ["brough"]}, "). The amount of cavity chipping is\ndetermined by the Chip Amount (", {"type": "code", "text": ["chip"]}, ") input. By increasing the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["chip"]}, "\namount, you can make the stone look more porous. Additional displacement\ncan be passed in through the Bump Amount (", {"type": "code", "text": ["bump"]}, ") input. For an example of\nhow ", {"type": "code", "text": ["bump"]}, " is used, see the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/stonewall", "type": "link", "text": ["Stone Wall"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/stonewall"}, " operator."], "extent": [190, 689]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Pepper"]}, " inputs refer to the additional color noise that is\n", {"type": "q", "text": ["peppered"]}, " over the stone surface to make it look more realistic. The\nlook of the pepper noise is controlled by three inputs: Pepper Amplitude\n(", {"type": "code", "text": ["pamp"]}, "), Pepper Roughness (", {"type": "code", "text": ["prough"]}, "), and Bump Frequency (", {"type": "code", "text": ["bfreq"]}, "). The\nPepper Color (", {"type": "code", "text": ["peppercolor"]}, ") specifies its color."], "extent": [689, 1020]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the Position (", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ") input and the Normal (", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, ") input are not connected,\nthe global variables by the same names will be used instead. Typically\nyou will use ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "type": "link", "text": ["Rest Position"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}, " or ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg", "type": "link", "text": ["UV Space Change"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg"}, " as inputs for ", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ", and\nwill not touch ", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, " unless you want to apply additional displacement to\nthe stone surface using an operator such as ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise", "type": "link", "text": ["Bump Noise"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise"}, ". If you need to\naccess the global variables directly, they are available from the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."], "extent": [1020, 1552]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1552, 1561], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/concrete", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/concrete"}], "extent": [1561, 1587]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/marble", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/marble"}], "extent": [1587, 1611]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}], "extent": [1611, 1636]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/stonewall", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/stonewall"}], "extent": [1636, 1663]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/stucco", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/stucco"}], "extent": [1663, 1688]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Stone"], "summary": ["Simulates a rough, non-descript stone material."]}